Package oogasalad.editor.controller

Class EditorObjectQueryHandler

java.lang.Object
oogasalad.editor.controller.EditorObjectQueryHandler
public class EditorObjectQueryHandler extends Object
Handles querying editor objects, including retrieval by ID and finding objects at specific coordinates.

  • Method Details

    • getEditorObject

      public EditorObject getEditorObject(UUID objectId)
      Retrieves the EditorObject associated with the specified UUID from the data API.
      Parameters:
      objectId - The UUID of the editor object to be retrieved.
      Returns:
      The corresponding EditorObject, or null if not found, ID is null, or an error occurs.

    • getObjectIDAt

      public UUID getObjectIDAt(double worldX, double worldY)
      Retrieves the UUID of the highest-priority object located at the specified world coordinates. Checks object hitboxes and considers layer priority for overlapping objects.
      Parameters:
      worldX - The world X coordinate to check.
      worldY - The world Y coordinate to check.
      Returns:
      The UUID of the object at the location, or null if no object exists there or an error occurs.

    • findHittingObjects

      private List<UUID> findHittingObjects(double worldX, double worldY)
      Finds all objects whose hitboxes contain the given world coordinates.
      Parameters:
      worldX - The world X coordinate.
      worldY - The world Y coordinate.
      Returns:
      A list of UUIDs of objects hit at the specified coordinates.

    • sortCandidatesByLayerPriority

      private void sortCandidatesByLayerPriority(List<UUID> candidates)
      Sorts a list of object UUIDs based on their layer priority in descending order (highest priority first).
      Parameters:
      candidates - The list of UUIDs to sort.

    • objectCollidesWithPoint

      private boolean objectCollidesWithPoint(EditorObject obj, double worldX, double worldY)
      Checks if an object's hitbox contains the given world coordinates. Assumes hitbox coordinates represent the top-left corner.
      Parameters:
      obj - The EditorObject to check. Can be null.
      worldX - The world X coordinate.
      worldY - The world Y coordinate.
      Returns:
      true if the point is within the object's hitbox, false otherwise or if object/hitbox is null.
